author: Pablo Picasso
message: I am always doing that which I can not do, in order that I may learn how to do it.
title: Thought of the day

author: Niccolo Machiavelli
message: Men in general judge more from appearances than from reality. All men have eyes, but few have the gift of penetration.
title: Thought of the day

message: You may only be someone in the world, but to someone else, you may be the world.
title: Thought of the day

author: Henry Ward Beecher
message: Every artist dips his brush in his own soul, and paints his own nature into his pictures.
title: Thought of the day
